 730:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****             /* The following assertion will fail if a service routine (ISR) for
 731:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * an interrupt that has been assigned a priority above
 732:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * configMAX_SYSCALL_INTERRUPT_PRIORITY calls an ISR safe FreeRTOS API
 733:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * function.  ISR safe FreeRTOS API functions must *only* be called
 734:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * from interrupts that have been assigned a priority at or below
 735:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * configMAX_SYSCALL_INTERRUPT_PRIORITY.
 736:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              *
 737:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * Numerically low interrupt priority numbers represent logically high
 738:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * interrupt priorities, therefore the priority of the interrupt must
 739:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * be set to a value equal to or numerically *higher* than
 740:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * configMAX_SYSCALL_INTERRUPT_PRIORITY.
 741:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              *
 742:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * Interrupts that  use the FreeRTOS API must not be left at their
 743:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * default priority of  zero as that is the highest possible priority,
 744:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * which is guaranteed to be above configMAX_SYSCALL_INTERRUPT_PRIORITY,
 745:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * and  therefore also guaranteed to be invalid.
 746:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              *
 747:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * FreeRTOS maintains separate thread and ISR API functions to ensure
 748:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * interrupt entry is as fast and simple as possible.
 749:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              *
 750:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * The following links provide detailed information:
 751:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * https://www.FreeRTOS.org/RTOS-Cortex-M3-M4.html
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccl1jRhL.s 			page 35


 752:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM3/port.c ****              * https://www.FreeRTOS.org/FAQHelp.html */
